\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid525380 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What is your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Westlea, Cunningsburgh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Are you married or a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I'm a widow. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you tell me the year of your marriage please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 1937.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 The place you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Mid Voxter, Cunningsburgh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How far is that from here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh it's about - two miles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Down south way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Down south way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How many years did you live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh I lived - thirty years, I was thirty years when I married. But we lived - when our - when the - when our house was building new we were up along the road at another wee house. Yes, yes. We - we built the new house in 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did other people help to build that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, well there was three employed to build you see and then they got quite a lot of help with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you know roughly how old your mother and father were when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I was thinking back and they would be about forty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They were about the same age themselves were they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, mother was four years younger than father. Four years younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did he come from Cunningsburgh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Fladdabister. One of the oldest places in Shetland. He belonged there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was your mother from there too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, she was from the Clifts in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 Cunningsburgh.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  Yes she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 as.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your father have a croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 At Fladdabister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, I - when he married. It's really my mother's croft but the old lady gave it to my father you see, they were staying with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your father do any other work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh he was a fisherman. And then sometimes he would get work in the fish yard, herr
ing curing. So he was always employed and then he did maintenance works on the roadways you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was that for a council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, for the county council. County council. So he was always employed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 He wasn't out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, I never remember him our of work, he was very fortunate like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were a lot of people out of work at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well, you see, they all had their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 crofts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  so they were ne'er - no unemployed, it was not like - today and I mean here we don't understand how they work as they do south.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Because they can get something from the land?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Because they - yes, they always had their land and then they always fished. Inshore fishing you see so you'd plenty of lovely fresh fish all the time. And they had their own sheep for killing in the wintertime you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did he fleece his own sheep, take the wool off them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. Oh the whole family could do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How did they do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They card the sheep you see and - got them in from the hill and put them
 in a small enclosure, and they plucked it, ruing we call it ruing with the hard. But it's - that was the fine wool but there are very few sheep nowadays they can pluck. Wool is changed, it's rougher and - there are more - bigger breeds of sheep and now t
hey shear it, and have the shears you know. There's still a few that can be - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
 plucked but it's a very fine Shetland wool that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you do that as a child, pluck the sheep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. Quite often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you do other things to help on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, we always used to work. Working in the peat, to raising up the peats after father was cutting the peat you know. He cut the peat.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How did he then carry the peats back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They carried them into carts, you know, in carts then we brought them home, carted them home with a little horse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you think of anything else you did, did you do any cutting of hay or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 We didna do the cutting but we did all the field spreading and the building and the combing and dry
ing the hay, oh yes, the children always did. From the age of maybe six years old you were always doing some little job about the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you have certain things that were specially your job or did everyone share the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, we shared the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You weren't told you must do this that and the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no, we sort of shared work, mother said would we go to hay today. Well we would all go you see. All work. Rake or corn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Inside the house did you do anything to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, we learned - we learned to knit and spin and - and - wash the dishes And all that you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 All the things in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 All the housework they teach us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your mother teach you baking in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do the children still learn to bake and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I think a few of them. Yes, more or less. And the boys learn the same as the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They learn baking do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, my brothers could cook as well as - as the sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I think you said your father used to cook too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh yes, he did. And I know quite a lot of men of his age who did the same you know. Look after the - yes, and we used to have nice big suppers then, but not that now. It's just a cup of coffee or a cup of milk but - in the old day
s you'd potatoes and quite a good feed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 At about what time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well from eight to ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was that after the day's work was done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Then they had quite a good feed then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you were a child at home was there just you at home or did you have a granny or a lodger or anyone with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
No, we had a - well we called her granny, she really was just - well she was no relation. But she owned the croft you see. My mother as a child did help her and she met with her well she ju
st stayed with us. We children knew her as a granny. But she just sat around the house, she was one of the family. And we used to have great fun, I think they lose a lot now with no grannies around the house. Yes, because learn to about old age and granny
 took you down if you got too high up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And there was another knee to sit on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes. And she would tell us the old tales you know as far as she could mind back. So that's how Shetland has a lot of that old tales, they're old people was at home with them all the time you see and you're hearing it and you just accepted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did she live with you through the 1914/18 war or had she died by that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, she - her husband died in the 1914 war. And he had a great experience as a young man. He l
eft Shetland as a young boy of seventeen you see, went to sail, he thought he would seek his fortune. Well he was very lucky the first ship or two and then they were in the Baltic and the skipper said, well we're going a longer voyage this time. They were
 going out to America. But he didn't tell the crew, you see, that the boat that they were sailing was - was already sold. When they came to America they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 shanghaied}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  and they just were on the beach you see. And he had to - they just had to do anything th
at they could, at last he got a ship, a Mexican ship. Went off in this Mexican ship and went down the east coast of America you see and around the cape. He was wrecked off the Magellan Straits. In the Magellan Straits. And - he - didn't know if he was ali
v
e when he found himself on the beach you know, they were dismasted and hauled up. He found himself on a beach. And when he came to himself he heard a queer noise and he looked round and there were an awful different lot of people all around and he thought
 
he was home in Shetland. But this - and they all had spears and bows and arrows and they were standing in a circle around him and he just feigned that he was dead you see. He could do nothing else. And then eventually after a long silence he said they sta
r
ted to poke him and prod him with their feet you see. And then after that he said he looked up and their faces was fairly different. They wasna so hostile. And he tried to get up and he couldn't, you see. And he lived for a year and a half with the native
s, on a small island in the Magellan Straits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How did they treat him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh, he said, once that they came to him they gave every kindness. They all sat around the fire and they slept round this fire at night you know. It's a wild life and they eat herbs when they fish. And he fished with them, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 menfolk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
 you see. And he was a tall man, six foot three, and - and this was a little kind of Indians race there. And then - he always looked for a ship, he just prayed if he could see a British ship. But he'
d given up all hope and one day they sighted a shop coming round - a kind of - a calm wintry day, so - and - and then they waved and he incited them to wave and shout and somebody in the crows nest spied him and he shouted, there's a white man with the na
tives. And the Captain hove to. And they took him on board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And he got away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
He - yes. And the skipper said, how did he come to be among this - he said, what nationality? He said, I'm British. The skipper couldn't believe it, he said, how did you
 come to be among the natives? It was only then they knew the - the end of that ship. And he had drifted on half a broken most, because he found the mast after on the island. But he said, they ate all - when they ate the dogs then he said, the one thing h
e couldn't eat. And he always took a walk around the island. But there were no contact with outside world. Wasn't it strange.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did she tell you about that herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 He telled us. Yes. Oh we sat and listened to that as children at his - on his knee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So he lived with you too as well as the granny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. He died in 1916. He was an old man then, ninety-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was he away at sea a lot of the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh he was at sea all the time. He was at sea all the time. And that didn't alter. I
 mean, he came home he was two years away, he went again. He sailed down, I think he was in his fifties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 He liked the seafaring life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you were a child was the washing done at home or did people send it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Always do - done at home. In a big wooden tub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was it done any day or was there always a set day of the week for washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, it was more when the weather was suitable. They did try and keep to a day, you know, the first two days of the week or that but t
hat wasn't any - they wouldn't wash until they got suitable - and in a big wooden tub called a sae in Shetland. Sae.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you knit your own clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Our stockings but not the dresses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was the underwear knitted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  underwear. Oh the children's underwear, yes, bairns with wooden vest. And the petticoat, they knitted petticoats. But not the outside - that was usually serge or something like that, that was bought material, tartan.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You bought the material and then who made the clothes in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh there were quite a few dressmakers in that time. In the village they were quite good. And they - they were made and they didn't charge very much. I mind having a dress made for a shilling. I can see it yet, it was blue,
 nice little blue cotton. Gingham, it was gingham really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your mother make any clothes herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Sometimes. Yes, she could do - maybe not the fine dresses but underwear and all that she did do. Petticoats and like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was there any special time of the year when new clothes were bought or ordered from the dressmaker.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It was mair if there was a wedding on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They got new clothes for a wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, a wedding. If it was at all possible they had a new dress for a weddin
g. Because they were big affairs the weddings you know, well it was the only entertainment much that was then a days. Weddings and a dance at Christmas or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How were the shoes got then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well those you bought in the shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Readymade or made to measure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 
Oh they - they weren't shoemakers in the district but that was more or less for older people that would have shoes that would wear longer you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  shoes were bought you see. And sometimes i
n summer we wore rivalins. That's - cow hide. Yes, made from cow hide. In the summer more or less - and yet they were awful comfortable. They were laced with thongs over your feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What about clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, I wore clogs. Little clogs, but not to go to school or that, just around the - around crafting. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 It were an awful thing wearing the clogs. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But the older folk had them quite regular. They were quite handy. The clogs, 'cos you just left them at the door.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they put on anything else indoors or walk in their stockings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well - yes, you see knitted - sort of knitted things they would put on, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 A sort of a slipper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, sort of a knitted slipper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 A sort of thing like they wear in Sweden, a tight fitting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, a tight fit, yes. And sometimes they would have a pair of clogs just specially for in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you tell me about repairing the shoes, did the fathers do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 In the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your father do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did he ever tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. Yes, he kept us all that old stories. He was very entertaining, he always played the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 accordion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  you see, and we danced in - maybe in the barn. All the village would come along and take part in
 it. Set up 'til two o'clock in the morning and then they'd go again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was that in the summer time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, in the winter. In the winter, we were always busy in the summer, there were none of that in summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Because people were working too hard in the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes, they were working and getting in crops you see and working at the fishing and it was only in - in - winter they started to - frivolities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You have the very long nights don't you in winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, we have long.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did anybody in the family play a fiddle, your brothers or you or your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. We could all you know pick a tune almost out of any instrument but we werena good - we could play - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 accordion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  and that but not to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 anybody}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  to dance to in any sense, but father was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you sing ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, we all sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you sing in a group together or by yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well I don't - in the choir we sang in groups and also in solos, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you sing in the evenings too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, there 
were a lot of sing songs around the homes you see. Or recitations or telling stories or forfeits - we all gathered more or less in the houses together you know and it was very jolly. It was more the boys that played the fiddle, there was some women that c
ould play the fiddle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How many homes were there round about that you visited or the people came to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh the whole of Cunningsburgh. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They all knew everybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you still today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, but not - not to s
uch an extent. Younger ones are not the same. They used to go all together and - 'cos there are more attractions now, the television and all this modernising you se, we had to make our own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Would you have been in everybody's house at sometime or other do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It must have been so friendly and nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, well there's not a home here that I've not been in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So everyone knows you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh everyone. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did anybody ever pay anyone for helping in the house with housework then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Well - no? I think well if there was an old lady stayed with you and she got her food and her rent they would give her wool and they would give her gifts and maybe a few shillings for it was really very seldom that they w
ould ever pay her like that. And you helped the neighbours, they weren't - if you - if you werena finished your crafting your work well then the neighbour would come and you would all practically finish up the one time. You left nobody out like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you remember your mother being ill so she couldn't do the work in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 She had good health did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, she'd good health.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did she ever have a paid job before she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, she went to the fishing you know, the gutting. The herring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It was women's work, they could do that could they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes, they could do - oh yes, they went round all Shetland and Shetland was a big fishing industry then. Stations all over the islands, up in Unst. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6513415\charrsid13915736 Quite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  a few stations here. That's all away now. And they went right around the island. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 
Sometimes they went from here to Minescroft, to Ness where your husband has gone. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They would go on a fishing boat round the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Working round the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. And stayed there and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was that all the year round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, it was just in summer, well down to maybe - end of September or October.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 In the winter did she get another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. She just stayed at home and knitting and working around the croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When she got married, did she have any other job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Just working in the croft. And the wool and the - the knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did she knit clothes and exchange them at the shop for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 goods}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Oh yes, they knitted in shops you see and they got a sort of
 a barter. They got some money and then they would get their messages. Or they got material for the - for - tea and sugar and all the groceries. Yes, they did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did the girls who were still at school do that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes. When I was five years old I could knit little mittens. You started the little mittens and then you - you grew as you - as you grew you did bigger things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did the boys ever knit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Some of them did. My youngest brother's quite a good knitter but I - I canna remember my brother Willy knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was he an older brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 He has the one older than me, but the youngest one could fairly knit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did he sell any of his things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. And quite a few of his chums then, young boys, 
maybe twelve year old, they were knitting and then they would buy their own shirts. Oh it was quite a help you see, they didna need -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So the knitting wasn't considered to be just for women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you remember when the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 Fair Isle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  patterns first came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, me mother made the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 Fair Isle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  patterns when I was a child but she made it in the Shetland colours. And then you see it went out of fashion for a long time. But when it come back again - in the first world war or after the first wo
rld war, she could knit that patterns right away with the brighter colours. So it always was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 Fair Isle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  patterns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Just the differences being the colour?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But they didn't do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But - I never - no, I never remember them doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did she have any medicines or remedies she used to make if you were ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh I've seen them say - oh - onions for sore throats. Slice an onion and put it round your throat. Yes, I remember one or two of that, old remedies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did she make gruel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh that's for - brochin? Thin and - yes, yes, we called it a brochin. Brochin, yes. Yes. For colds. And to warm you up if you were being chilly, and you made a brochen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you remember any tinned food in those days as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. Can't say I ever saw tinned food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No tinned corned beef or that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 On the croft there were sheep, were there any hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. Flock of hens. We'd eggs and then - the - sold eggs and got them barter too. Groceries you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you eat eggs for any meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What meals did you have eggs for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Well for the breakfast, Sunday we always had a - a duck's egg, yes. They're bigger. Yes, I mind a duck's egg on Sunday. But we had - always had ducks too. When w
e were little ones we just got a half egg. It was - cutting in two you know and each got a half egg, it's too big for the little ones. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you have any goats, did they keep goats round here at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Goats? No, I never remember them when I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And did you have a pig?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, the difference was the colour, they didn't used the bright colours, that was introduced like after this first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 If you went to visit people did you knit as you walked along or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do people still do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Very seldom. You'll see one or two of the older folk maybe knitting maybe on a lovely day. Yes. Everybody knitted as they }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 walked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  - if they were going to - if they were working - if the hayfield was a good bit away, 
maybe a quarter of a mile or that, they would take their stuff and knit away on the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 In the museum I saw a model of an old fire with the pot on top, is that how you cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes. And a Dutch oven, another pot you know and - more shallow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 With a lid on top?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, and they baked in that. Laid the coals on the top and - and underneath. Made lovely bread. Made lovely bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your mother bake every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Not every day but every second day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did she do anything like making jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Just rhubarb. Made quite a lot of rhubarb jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they make pickles, pickled onions or cabbage or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, it was all fresh. Yes. Never saw that kind of think in them days no. That was in the garden you know and
 we just had it - cabbage all winter and the turnips.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 She didn't put things in bottles to keep them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did she or your father make any beer or wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. But I've seen them making the home brewed as we used to call it. With hops 
and - Yes, always had one pig every year. Just came as a little pig you know and grew and then that was cured and - the hams hung on the roof and dried. It was lovely.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you use it all yourself or did you sell some of it or give some away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, had a big family, we used it all ourselves. Oh maybe any friend who didn't have a pig we give a bit too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But it wasn't for selling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, no. No. It was just for home consumption then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And you had one or two cows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Had three cows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you milk at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, when I was maybe ten years old I could milk the cows. Or maybe a little earlier by the time I could milk the cow well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you have sheep to salt and have in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. They salted them and sometimes they hanged them up. But sometimes you just kept them in the salt, like salt them down. Lovely.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They were nice were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How did they cook them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well they boiled them longer you know, they were boiled and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Like salt beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes, like salt beef, wait before you put in the vegetables. They used to boil that and then - see if it was too salt and put in a second water and then the vegetables. I - I thought it was lovely, I love it yet. I love the salt, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you still have salt mutton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes, but it's not so common now they all have the deep freeze and I don't think that that's half so good.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you get any rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, no. It was farm but I didn't like rabbits so we didn't - I canna say that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You don't fancy rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I don't fancy today even. But we'd plenty of fish, all different kinds, lovely fish. Lovely fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Caught by your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Caught, yes. Or the neighbours, if the neighbours was out and he wasn't off well we'd get - well - meal to a fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you salt your own fish ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh yes. Salt our - cure them - keep them for a standby in case it was rough weather you know. You wouldn't by on salt fish but if it was rough weather you couldn't get - then you'd have the salt fish for a - emergency.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was there ever a shortage of food in your family as there was in some families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. I never - no - I never remember - a shortage and I never remember a neighbour having a shortage. You se, that having th
e crofts. There was no money, there was no circulation of money. But we didn't seem to miss it because you see you give your eggs and you got groceries, you give your hosiery and you got material for your dresses or groceries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So you don't remember any children who seemed to be going hungry or short of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I never do you know, no, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were you allowed to talk at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. But if a stranger was coming in then we weren't to be impertinent and - monopoly sit and b
it more quiet and realize and I think it was - did us a lot of good. Because I mean - we were never - we used to play and the noise was terrible and I - I just wouldn't have been able to stand about a half of what granny stood. 'Cos we were climbing on he
r back and shouting and the neighbours was in and - and mother was away outside you know and we made some awful noise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 At mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh, not in the mealtime, not in the mealtime, no, we - we sat more quiet then, oh yes, and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you tell me if there were any rules about how you were to behave at meals and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Well yes, they would tell you they don't - not to eat too quickly and that and if anybody's around - and behave and not leave the table until - you asked to leave. If you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You had to ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. May I leave the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 If you didn't want to eat your food on the plate what did they say then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh you just had what was set afore you and you must eat up. You can't eat that you can't eat the next. And w
e ate - and I believe it was quite right because - children say can you have this can you have the next, can you - and it's foolish. Because when you come out in the world you just have to eat what is set before you. For the most part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 If you wanted to bring a toy or a book to the table could you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, I never - no, I never saw - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Could you ask for more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You were allowed to ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, it was - the plates set down on the table, you helped yourself. Yes, yes, there's no restrictions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It was quite free?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you always have the same place at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no. No, anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When grown ups were around were you allowed to talk in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, but - oh we were allo
wed to talk but if there were any strangers in we weren't allowed to make a nuisance of ourselves that they couldna - hear. We wasna allowed to get up - and mother sat quiet.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you remember if you were ever punished for anything, if you did anything }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 naughty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh yes, I was often punished, I was an awful tom-boy. I got many a lash around the legs. Yes, but - but just for mischief. We would just get up to all tricks. We would go into barn, maybe tumble up the corn and - it's a wonder that we didn't get more.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What would you get a smack with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
With a hand or a bit or rope or anything that came that you - you hit across the legs with. You didn't seek it the second time though. But we used to climb in the seashores you know and high on the c
liffs. Oh it was - I couldna look at the places I used to climb in. And any neighbour that come for you, you see, there'd be more trouble. Anyone that came just knocked or slapped anyone right and left, they didna just hurt their own children. They correc
ted the neighbours - yes, the neighbour would correct you if you were doing wrong while you were in his house just - and they never quarreled about that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I suppose it was what they liked really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Sort of a community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, if we
 went next door and - and - and was riotously when we were playing well that lady would just give us a smack too. And mother thought it - they did quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Is it like that today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No. it's not like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 If you were ever hit by another child what were you expected to do, if you told your mother would she tell you to hit the child back or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
No. Oh she would say not to but we never consulted her, we hit back. She would tell us not to but - we children never consulted her. Well 
you see, cuts two ways, if a child is staying back all the time and somebody hitting him, he must hit back. Definitely. Because if you didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 The other boys don't appreciate you sitting all quietly do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, no, they don't, no, no, you must - you must - so we did that, we hit back I'm sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What sort of behaviour did your parents expect from the children towards them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well I - what do you exactly mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Some parents liked their children to be very close to them and tell them 
their worries, that sort of thing, and others liked them to keep rather far apart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh yes. Yes. Oh no, they werena - they still - they werena - asking us to - to forcing our confidence you know. But - mother, we could tell her anything, father the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You were close to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Very easy. And father was just the same. He is good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they talk about how you should behave towards your sisters and brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I 
canna say I ever heard a lecture on that, we seemed to - you seemed to accept that you had to be decent towards them but then sometimes we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 weren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 . We would fight. Oh we would - scratch one another you know, or - while - if mother had to settle the quarrel we both got a lick. I mean, we were no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 angels}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  we were children and we were playing and we were fighting then the next minute we'd be quite all right with each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was there one brother or sister that you were particularly friendly with in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Well I think I - I was more friendly with both my brothers because there was one just above me and one below. And I thought them far better then the other ones. It maybe was being just nearer in age and so - I did like them the best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you remember birthdays in those days, were they different from other days or were they just like any ordinary day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, they were just like any other ordinary day. You might get a little - bread or sweet cake baked for you and that. And they would say, 
this is your birthday. You maybe get a - something sweet for your tea or something a bit different, but there was no special - no, there were no special celebrations then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No people specially coming to the house on that day or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no. No, no. Not in these days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How was Christmas Day spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh Christmas Day was a jolly day and no work done except for feeding the cows or that that had to be done. And you were visiting the whole time and your house was full of visitors and they 
always had - there was no cakes much then. But then there was special - well it's like - what would you call plum pudding. And oh there were big plum pudding made, it was awful size in big pot. And that was nearly everybody come in got a piece of the plum
 pudding and - some drinks. There were drinks. In Christmas time, but that was about the only time that they had their festivities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they go to the church on Christmas Day or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No. No. Didn't at that - they don't to that much now unless in Lerwick or that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your mother and father play any games with you like cards or snakes and ladders when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, oh yes, snakes and ladders. Father could play cards but not mother. But he played cards. Oh yes, we played cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you play }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  other games indoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh - we played everything. When we were children, running around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Chasing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, chasing one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you have any hoops or anything like that or balls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh you've seen the great
 big cartwheels - well you got a hoop off that and beating that way with a stick down the road. Yes, we were a menace sometimes get a lot of old cartwheels. Everyone with a stick and beating it along to see who would keep it the longest running. And we di
d
 that - and we used to go a lot at the boats in the sea. That was danger - but we always - yes, we used to go down boats and - and oars you know. They would never be allowed to do that now. 'Course we were doing and they were too busy to be seeing everyth
ing we were doing. We came to no accident but we could have you know. 'Cos it really wasna game for children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you remember a funeral in the family before 1918 or what a funeral was like then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, the funerals, they used to have drink at funer
als. I remember I - well then that was the custom and an old man explained to me, I always wondered and I said, why did you have this liquor at the - well, he says, you know, when somebody's coming maybe three miles to walk to a funeral on a cold winter d
ay, he said, that's how they gave them a glass of whisky, strong big glass of whisky. 'Course they were carrying the funerals then you know, there was no transport, no hearses. And they had this special wood that its planted then -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 On their shoulders they carried it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes, they carried it on - and they changed places, the six that was carrying well the next six would come up and you know this is turned back you see. And they took it in turns like that, the whole company carried. But they would - u
sed to give them drink before they left the house. Give them a glass of whisky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they carry any drink with them to go to the cemetery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Not here, but some did. In some places they did. You see, it never was so much distance here. Never more th
an three miles here. But some of the places farther north where they had to carry them miles then, then the nearest relatives carried the whisky on them you see, and gave them refreshments after a mile or two miles walk. But it was not necessary in - in t
his district because - near you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did the women go to the cemetery, the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Well very seldom. They do now. Yes. They didn't then, no. No, no, they didn't. They were at the funeral service in the house. Oh yes, all the relatives, womenfolk. But not out of the house. And they stayed for the menfolk come back from the churchyard.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you have a newspaper then in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, there was the Shetland - Journal, but there was the Shetland Times come out -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was that before the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes, in the first war in the papers they had a - a leaflet every day, they called it the Special, the War Special. And my mother read that War Special. She was a great reader. I mean her years, there were few which could read fluently. But 
she had an old uncle that was a pupil teacher or something and he teached her. And the very old - the - all this old folk would gather in to hear this war Special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 She read aloud to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, she would read aloud you know. She would read aloud then - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 they
\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  say, she's an awful good reader. That old folk listened to this war specials.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Could most of those old folk read a little do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Maybe just a little bit you know, yes. But not fluently, not - not - not fluently, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your mother read books too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Very - quite a lot, she was awful well read. Awful well read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Shetland people seem to be keen on education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you think they are more than down south?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well they - they seem - they're awful well
 read. I think that's because all the menfolk, there's hardly a family, it doesn't have - people somewhere else in the world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So they're interested in the world and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. In every family there's son sailing or father sailing. An
d you go to know a few places in the world, you know, and you'd always find geographies in every house. Always, I never - I never remember a house there wasna somebody had a geography and they could tell in - and I think so much contact with the outside w
orld you see. I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you have quite a few books in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you remember of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Well you see there were a library and that library was run from the Manse. The library, it was a room in the Manse and I reme
mber them going and exchanging this books Coates library, the first ones that came out that was early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you belong to that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well anyone could go in the parish, anyone, it didna matter did you belong that church or not. That was for the parish and visitors, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was it free?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. You just got the book and then you put it back. Yes. It was gifted by Mr Coates of Aisley, that and the Manse.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you ever read aloud to your younger brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well maybe just the books at school you know. But that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you tell stories then to your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, we telled all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You all told stories did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, we telled stories handed down to us and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did other children round about tell stories too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, they all telled stories. Everyone. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 
I've seen them all gathered and sitting knitting you know and somebody would sing, maybe somebody'd recite. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
And you're doing - the knitting was carrying on the whole time and then the boys, some of them would come along and they would play the fiddle and do a dance, you know, in the kitchen floor you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you ever go away for a holiday before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was there ever a Bank Holiday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. Never had. They never - never had a Bank Holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When did you first hear of them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It was just a name you know, like, I maybe heard the name this is Bank Holiday because it's always marked on the big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6513415\charrsid13915736 calendars}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  you see. But it meant nothing further on the calendar, it was just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It was just an ordinary working day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It was just - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your father ever take you out on your own anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, he always went back to his home at Fladdabister and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6513415\charrsid13915736 his}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  friends and he would take us among all his relations you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You'd walk over?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 On the Sundays, yes, we'd walk over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you have any means of transport other than your feet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 None at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was there anybody in the neighbourhood who did have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well some -
 one or two had a gig you know. And if - if anybody needed to go to Lerwick, well, or a doctor or some peats you see, this old men would always go in the gig for speed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But generally you went everywhere by foot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Walk - walking to Lerwick and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You still can?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes, I walked it when I was eight years old to Lerwick. And back again the same day. You never thought - you just walk - walk the same you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you go to Sunday school when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes and the church too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was that the Church of Scotland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, the United Free Church. Yes. But there was a Church of Scotland too I mean but we went to the United Free Church ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did it have a temperance club or any temperance work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well I remember as a child some teenagers they said - total temp - or T.T. or something. Yes. Once but I don't think it lasted very long.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It wasn't a club with weekly meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no, no, no, it was just joining the pledge or something that they wouldna dri
nk or something. I don't think it really got off the ground much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your mother and father go regularly to church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. They went regularly and we had to go too. 'Course I didn't - I never felt it any effort or any - I once said, well 
I don't know that I'll bother with the kirk today. And mother said, oh - you think so. But I was just - I thought I wouldn't go to church but she said, oh you think so, but you see - and oh I've seen eight of us going together maybe, other children you kn
ow and - and some older person with us to sit in the seat and they usually put maybe four in front of them and then sat in the middle and then - just looking from right to left. She'd one look, it was enough for us, believe me it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 At the school did they - Shetland people seem to speak two languages, is this true?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Well yes, well we speak our own language here, Shetland until we go to school. But at school it's just English and we never questioned - they never said we'll keep up your own languag
e. We certainly delve back in time, keep up the older language but there's awful lot to have been lost in my days. An awful lot and it's a great pity because there were some lovely old words that English language doesn't express half so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were there little proverbs and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes there were an awful lot of Shetland proverbs. Some very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But the schools haven't kept it up, they don't do it in the schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No, there's no Shetland taught in the school and never was in my day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 If you talked Shetland in school what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no, no, you never - you just didn't do it. No, no, you just didn't do it, you didn't - you just accepted the English language.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What about if you used a Shetland word or two, for little they say peerie do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, peerie. No, he would just say, now that's not English.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They would say that to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, they would just say, that's not English. And you accept it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But you would say it at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, always spoke it at home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 In the church did you have a choir that you belonged to or did you not sing in a choir?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, we were in the choir. Sang in a choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did the choir have any special outings or treats, parties or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Not in the early times, now they do have them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They didn't then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did the Sunday school have a treat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, always had a picnic in the summer. These are the - they have them down in the sands and there always were a picnic. Then
 they would get money for the prizes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they have races for prizes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, races and - maybe gathering flowers or naming how many flowers you could name, they had quite a lot of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 competitions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  along and swings and all. It was a high day the pic
nic. And quite a few of the older people at the church came. The children did the races, but sometimes the older people would join in. Quite a big day, the picnic. They always had a picnic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 On Sunday in those days was it considered wrong to do work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You couldn't knit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no, no, I wouldn't knit yet on Sunday. I wouldn't touch knitting yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do most of the older people not knit on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 There are very few of the younger people even that knit. No, there are a few - no co
nnection with church but as a majority I don't think that ninety - three percent of the people would - touch knitting, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What about other work, cooking for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh you'd just cook the main dinner and that, I never saw a family making any d
ifference like that. But you prepared, you washed the potatoes or the turnips or anything like that and you did all the preparation that could be done the night before, you did it. And your shoes was brushed for Sunday school on Saturday night. And - and 
all the things that could be done that night and your water was fetched from the well, there was no piped water then you see. You had the well and you always brought in extra.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were the children bathed ready for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, always on Saturday night. On Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And they had to bring the water in from the well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It must have been quite a lot then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It was quite a lot of water. We all carried little pitchers of water and then they were put in a big tub to save for night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you heat the water for the bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. Heat it in a big pot - kettle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 On Sunday did you have special clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, and was laid by for next Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Never worn in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, never. Never for school or nothing. 
Just had the one dress for Sunday. It lasted you a long time but it was - then you were never - you were just having it on the Sunday you see so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Could you play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No - if we were catched - we did it on the quiet maybe but never - but no. It wasn't approved at all. No frivolity on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Could you read a book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Any book
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Or had it to be a religious one?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no. No. We could read, yes anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But you couldn't play cards or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 snakes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  and ladders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. Oh no, not - not any games. But I'm afraid there were a few played all the same but - regardless. But we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But it wasn't with your parents knowledge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. Oh no, it wasna.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Shetland is known for its Liberal voters isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes. Yes. That's - yes. Well, for thirteen year we had a Conservative. Before Mr Grimmond came in. Yes, thirteen years Sir Basil Spence, Spence was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you were a child can you remember your parents taking an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes. Mother was very keen on politics. Yes. Very keen. And - and father was the same - they were very - but her especially. And they voted Liberal and then - oh some years ago Robert Boothby came up here, a young man twenty-four years old and mother said,
 I'm going to give this young man a chance because I think he's worth-while. We've voted long enough that old Liberal. And she voted for him. And father still at that time kept to Liberal and I remember the minister coming in, he says, I believe William, 
we were in the same boat last time, both our women went off with the young - Boothby. And he said, well I think we'll just have to follow. Father says, I think we'll follow suit next time. So since then he voted Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 He didn't vote Liberal anymore after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I suppose that would have been around about 1920?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Women got the first vote in 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, that's right. I remember father awful keen to give the women the vote. And - yes, and - Pankhurst
 - Mrs Pankhurst. Oh he just admired this wife. He says, she was doing quite right. She should get the vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your mother think the same?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes, they were - they really were quite advanced for the - time. Yes, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What about their friends and neighbours, did they believe in votes for women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, I - I never heard anybody saying they shouldn't up here. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Perhaps because the women shared so much and worked so hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, might be you see, they shared.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They worked like men didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes they did, when the men was at the sea then the womenfolk had to carry on the croft you see in winter, and work on the croft, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 In some places at that time men felt that if they didn't voted the way that the
 landowner wanted or the employer they might lose their job or their house, did that happen round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well you see, there were - there were no tied houses in this district so it never happened in this district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 People didn't pay rent to the laird round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
They paid the rent for the croft but they were individuals you know, they - they'd a croft a rent act - to support them. But maybe anybody that was working directly to a laird, they would maybe curry favour you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Have you heard about that ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
No, heard - yes, I've heard, they would say, oh this old man, he's going to vote with the laird, he was - you know currying favour with the laird, but it was very seldom cases like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But not ever in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, never. I never heard of it in this district, you know, currying favour or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was there a laird round about here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Mr Bruce and his ancestors. There were one very bad one, John Bruce, but his - his brother Robert was a very nice man. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 This laird is a very, very nice man. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
So it was just the one in the family you would say made a black name for years for the rest. But they were no house as any of the rest of the lairds, they were all just, I mean, making the men fish for them and making t
he men work for them and at one time Shetland had to pay liberty money if any young men took as he'd go out south then he had to pay liberty money, a pound in a year before he was allowed out of Shetland with the lairds and that. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 As if they belonged to the lairds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes, well it was - it was - there were no law then to protect them like what's now. They fought against it eventually and they fought then but they just had to do it. The pound was on your rent. And they called that liberty money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did that happen in your family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
No, never in the family but that happened all around because there was a minister, a Mr Clarke, and when the commissioner come up here in 1886, 1889 it was, then he fought the people's cause against this y
ou see and he did the whole island they came flocking from all over the islands, the Church of Scotland ministers wouldn't help them, because you see they were sharing in big salaries, getting the Manses and churches repaired on this you see, they would l
ay it on the rent. If the Church of Scotland wanted a Manse }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 repaired}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
, oh put a pound on the rents. And it wasn't fair whether you belonged to the Church of Scotland or not. But you see that settled it in 1891 it was all done away with. Very much thanks to t
hat Mr Clarke that was here, the United free minister. He fought that case and he won it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did the laird and his wife and family mix at all with the people, did they mix and visit and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 In - in my young days? Oh no, you looked u
p to the laird, you kind of - you see, they're going by with their gigs and that, you didn't - no, they didn't mix, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They never called in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you meet them at the church ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well they would meet them but they'd no contact with you. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Would you greet them, say hello or how do you do or anything like that if you saw them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 Then days}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 ? No. No. But nowadays it's quite different you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you think there's more social equality in that way now?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 O
h yes, definitely. You respect the person for - of course, Shetland has no class. I mean class distinction. You don't know what such a thing. But you would give them - if they're a person in a position, you would respect their position. But outside of the
ir normal life they're just you and me. I mean, there are no class distinction in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 Shetland}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  whatsoever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was it like that when you were a child too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, that - the lairds and the minister, Church of Scotland minister and all were aloof. Yes, they w
ere aloof. 'Cos I can remember quite well that I know - I realize now that they were aloof.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But they're not now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They're not now. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were you brought up to call the minister sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well yes, we respect the minister definitely. 
Yes. But - yes, we answer them, yes, Mr Clarke was our minister that man that fought for the - and I remember saying yes sir, but he was an awful nice man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What about the shopkeepers, the merchants, were they called sir, were they respected or were they like the ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh no, there were some of them very nice and there were some of them that wanted to make money and they would join anything to get money. Then they were hated. Of course there was a lot of bad tenants too. The laird wasna
 just all the bad. Bad tenants that would do nothing and expected to pay nothing. Just the same as there are today you know. So I mean the laid had a - quite a lot to contend with tool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did the shopkeepers mix with the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. They were just ordinary - they were ordinary people around here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 walk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
 in your house and you'd walk in their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I just wondered if they were a separate class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They weren't like the ministers and the lairds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no. You see the shopkeepers are Shetland people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Just ordinary Shetland people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And the children all went to the same school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It's very different from England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 There are more distinctions there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, there are. No, we have - we tolerate no - distinction among families, only you give a man his honour where honour is due.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But that's a different thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Would you say among the ordinary people there were big differences in the standard of living, how people lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 In my young day? No, I don't think so. I think we were very much all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What about people who didn't have a croft, the cotters, were there cotters round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well there we
ren't so many but then they would work to the crofter you see. And they were - they would get taties and sometimes they would work - a rig we called it, a ditcher, a rig. They would get a bit of land and they would grow their own potatoes and vegetables. 
Y
es, I've seen that. Or exchanging it, oh you can have this, I'm not using it and - so I don't think the cotter was anything so different as what he is today. Now he's a separate unit and doesna maybe want but when they helped the crofters he more or less 
just lived as the crofters would you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 At the school were there any children who seemed much poorer than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. I never saw anybody different}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6513415\charrsid13915736  from when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  I was six. All just the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 The people who went to the different }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 churches}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 , the United Free and the Presbyterian, were they different kinds of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
No, they were just the same people but they just followed like - your father's church or your mother's church. Well you - they generally just followed them in that. But if th
ey marrying, the one from the one church, well they would just go to someone of the two churches. Never no - no difference or no stripe. No, if they had any special occasions on the churches well they would all go to that church if there weren't different
 service. And if they're having a soiree or a - a sing-song then you wouldna go to put it on both the one night you see so you'd opportunity to go to both places. That was always done here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you remember anyone being described as a real lady or a real gentleman when you were a child, did they use that expression?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh yes, if there was somebody that was awfully good and - and kind to everybody, they would say, that's a genuine lady or a genuine gentleman. He is a gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It meant how a person behaved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Behaved. It was their behaviour, it wasna their money. No, the money didn't account I mean to call you a gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you remember at that time people moving from one class to another, say to being minister from being an ordinary 
crofter or cotter or was it from certain kinds of families that people became ministers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
No, it was more religious families that would become a minister. But you would just look up to him as a minister but he would still be your neighbour. He never w
ent up like that. No. Teachers or anything, well they're all girls, the teachers They're just here and they come and do work on the croft when they - M.A's and all. 'Cos I remember a - one of ladies up up west of Buora Isle she said - I was amazed, she sa
ys, "Could you tell - is it true that this lady is a M.A.?" And I said, "yes," "And she's a B.Sc.?" "Yes." "Well you never said." So I said" - there are three of them sitting in this crowd that are B.Sc's. She said, "I got the surprise of my life." And }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 you\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  all one? I says, "We're all one - as neighbours."
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So the teachers didn't keep themselves aloof?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
They don't - they don't to this days. A teacher is no more as a crofter here. We don't consider them any better as a crofter. And I think that that's fine because you're all the same. And they join into the community you know, and they just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You're very lucky to live in a community like the aren't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, it's very nice because they can help so much you know, in the education and they certainly give it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It's nice for them too because they have more variety of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, and they know, I mean, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 In England and perhaps in Scotland too the teachers mix mainly with other teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, they don't to that here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They're friendly with everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 they\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  some of our boys they go away sailing when some of them goes in for their officer's ticket and takes their officer's ticket you see. Well they come home here, they just put on their dungarees and awa
y to the hill and working and - you'd never know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were there any families who were considered to be rough when you were a child, was it a word that was used about people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, well I - I - I only heard about one delinquent - he wasn't a delinquen
t, he should have - kind of a different boy that was put into what they called the school of correction then. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Like a reformatory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, sort of a reformatory. But nowadays he was just a - healthy robust boy, but not rough you know, or n
ot use a knife or anything like that. No, I never heard anybody -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You didn't hear it said about any certain families like they do in some part of the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. oh no. No, no, no. And if anybody was fallen a girl or that well you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 dinna}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  hold it against them, it's very rare case. I mean you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 dinna}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  - we don't - there are no dominants here, we never - but - I can't say I ever heard - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 People being called rough and looked down on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. Oh no, not. Not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So when you were a child there were no children that your parents told you not to play with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no, never. No. There are nobody like that, we never know what that is up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And there were no families who thought themselves superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, because they all - y
ou see, they would never get honour. They would ask maybe what stand, they would never get on with it because nobody would -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Nobody would take them seriously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, they were just give them no honour at all. No, they would it. But that's not to sa
y we don't appreciate anybody as is going to be teachers or sea captains or anything like that. We appreciate them doing that but just when they're back home here well they're just the same as - indeed they are that, they really are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was there a policeman round about in the area, on duty when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well there were - there were - no. There was one in Sandwick away down but he was just - you knew that he was there but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You didn't see him about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did anyone ever say to you when you were a child, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you ever remember anybody a person being driven out of their home by banging tin cans and making a terrible noise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Before you went to school did anybody teach you anything in the way of school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh yes. My mother buy me a little - it's a easel and - and I did marbles when we learned to count. And - I could always say - I could say the alphabet. Just the letters, learnt us the old way, yes we could do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 She did that for all of you did she before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How old were you when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I was nearly six.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Not very quickly. And we ran home four our dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You came home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Ran down the fields for a short cut.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You were quite near the school were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, we lived more than a mile away. But we came a short cut and made us that - made us about - little over half a mile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What time was school in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It was nine o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And what time was dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 For twelve to one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What time did it finish in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Four o'clock usually. Half past three in winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you first started school you went back in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes. Right away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was that what they call a board school in England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, it was just a - a government school. A government school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Not to do with the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were there girls and boys mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 altogether}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 , yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Right through until you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Right through, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 At what age did you leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I was nearly fifteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you went to school did you walk along with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. Three houses there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You all went along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, we all went. We the three children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And quite a few of your brothers and sisters went I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. There were always four. Yes, four when I went. No, five. Youngest five went together, but - can't remember the older two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you tell me what you thought about school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Well I rather liked it. I thought the teachers nice. But some didn't like it you know, for the first but - I - I mean I liked it and they were good teachers was very diligent at learning you whatever they could, they were very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Can you remember what the teachers considered very important, thinking of things like manners, tidiness or neatness, punctuality, did they think those things were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, t
hey thought that all that was important and you - very - they wanted that you were good writers and good readers and good at arithmetic. That was the most important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They worked on that a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They worked on that, really it wasna their blame if you werena quite good at either of that three subject.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 If you did something the teachers thought wrong what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well they'd warn you, they didn't knock you at first. If you just were repeating - repeatedly doing naughtiness then they w
ould - smack you. But - you would have; caused if they did, they really were nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They warned you first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes they did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they ever hit children with a strap or a cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Oh I got strapped too. Yes. Big leather }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 strap}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 For what sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
I was knocking or somebody was drawing - got a bit cheeky no doubt and this knocked over me and another girl having fun about - china vase, I remember I got three on each }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were there any other punishments at all, like putting children in the corner or keeping them after school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh yes, as standing - standing with your face to the wall if you maybe laughed and not - then stand near to the wall with your face to the wall and you didn't need to look round. You knew that the other children was laughing at you but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did your mother and father take an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they ask you what you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, and - and they made us read and - and do our lessons as soon as we came home and then play after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You had home lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. We had home lessons and we had to do that first and then play after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they ever visit the school in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Visit? No. No I never remember any parents. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they know the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh yes, they knew the teachers and they would contact them - outside you know, going through the village or that, they knew them quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But they didn't go up to the schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No, not in my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you remember the teachers picking out any children for different treatment from others?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Well I can't say I ever saw that although some children thought that there were favourites, you know, others were favourites but I think it was if a child wa
s clever then they would say, oh they like him best, but I - I don't think that they were. I'm not saying it couldn't be but - I don't remember it myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you remember any children being more harshly treated that others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, they never - I never saw anybody doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They were fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They were very fair the teachers. Yes, I will say that, I couldn't say that I ever saw them -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were there any gangs or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 cliques}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  among the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No. Not such a thing, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you remember any children who were left out of things, on their own, lonely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
No. I can't say I ever saw a child left. We might have been - awful - chums with this one next day but then next day we might be chums with the one you see just the dead opposite, ther
e were no cliques, they were just - I never saw them - any children left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Any children alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No, I never did see that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you go to any other school or evening classes after you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, I went to evening classes, all eveni
ng classes. English and - and arithmetic and sewing and needlework. Yes, always went there, and cookery classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 For how long did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh for years. For I was nearly married. They all did that, they always went to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 People were so keen on learning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, and boys went to navigation classes right on even -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was that at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Evening classes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 At the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, at the school. We always got a retired captain or something to take the navigation. If the s
choolmaster wasna qualified they'd always have some captain that was retired and - home he would take the classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 If you could have stayed at school longer would you have done so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You were quite happy to leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
I was quite happy to leave. I had nothing else to learn at school and I was - and I was fair - fair average, I mean, I was quite - but I can't say that I would have any desire to be a teacher or anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No, I can't say that I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You were quite happy about your schooling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes. 'Cos after you leave school, I mean, the grounding that you got at school is really only a beginning. I mean, you read and - you're educating yours
elf the whole time. Your whole life, yes. The school was a good grounding and - and everything that was necessary in that times you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 While you were at school did you ever earn any money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh - knitting. Yes, I earned - bought clothes of my own you know by knitting at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did children get any money for getting messages from the shops or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, I never got a penny. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you get pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. There didn't seem to be much money then but we never seemed to miss it. Oh maybe on an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 occasional}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
 maybe somebody would say, I'll give you a penny, you're worth a penny. But that was a rare occasion. If you ran messages for any neighbour you know, for a person you never - your mother wouldn't allow you to take a penny. Yo
u were taught not to take money from older people you'd help them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It was considered wrong?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you left school did you get a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you tell me what it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I - I went to the fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Like your mother had done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you tell me a bit about it, what the hours were and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Well hours were - well I've seen us working - if it's a big catch of fish in just to let the boats off again I've seen us working up to midnight. Star
ting at six. But you never seemed to mind, you had your meal hours and there's so many girls, maybe a hundred of you on the one - yard you know in the troughs and - and you were young, you never minded that. In the later years it came that you were finish
ed at the latest at nine if it's a big fishing and off at six and ten at nights you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you work on Saturday too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you get a half day off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, Monday - after six, that was our half day. And then you had to do your wa
shing and - and prepare your meals, you're living you know six girls - to the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 On the ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
On the - stage on the seashore, yes, and on at Lerwick and you'd two big rooms, a big bedroom and a big kitchen living room. And if this - your half
 holiday after six you had to do all your washing and - for the next week you know. Yes, that's our half a day. And when we were down Yarmouth and Lowestoft way, then we were at the lodgings you see and hours were shorter there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So you went all round the coast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you go down to Cornwall?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, I never was there but I - some of the girls that I was with - was there. I never was further south than Yarmouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So this was in the summer months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Summer and - in Lerwick. In Sh
etland. But Lowestoft and Yarmouth was later in - in the winter. We come home at Christmas. Before Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was there any time of the year when you weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. Then we were knitting. The Christmas before we started the next - May, first of May.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So you had about three or four months in the year off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes, and we knitted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And then you started again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was it an interesting life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It was, very interesting. It was and you were with the girls you made such friends, I still write to that girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Girls who you met in other places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Still write.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you went to places like Yarmouth and Lowestoft did you meet other people who lived there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you go to dances and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Britannia Pier was the rage then, Britannia Pier, Yarmouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Do you remember when you first went south, did it seem very different from Scotland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well we'd read }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 a lot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  about - only time I not - the train. Th
e train, it's funny in the train and I was used such a look at the different place, I could tell every place I been from - well from Berwick on Tweed right down to Yarmouth. Potter Heigham and all that - Northam, oh, Kings Lynn and all the places we went 
through, I remember that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you tell me who supervised you in that work, did you have a supervisor or somebody over you, a forewoman or someone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 Well, yes, a foreman, a cooper and they did their work and then we did the gutting and the packing you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And there was always one of that coopers supervising your work. Yes, cooper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were you supervised a lot, did they give you a lot of orders or did you just get on with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. They were very nice. Yes, they were very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you got paid, how much was it, was it the same the whole year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well it was piecework you see. Big fishing you'd a big pay day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was it done by the piece of the fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 The piece - the barrels, the - with the barrels you see. Three of you worked t
ogether, two gutting and - and one packing. And then you shared that equally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You shared the money out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You shared the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Can you remember what sort of money you would get for a good catch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh some years - well - I'm seeing myself
 with thirty or forty pound in something like two or three months. It was big money then. Yes, big money. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was it the most popular work here abouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Here in Shetland it was because of the fishing area. It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you first started off did you know girls who were going too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, I went with girls from here you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So you weren't among strangers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, not then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you got the money did you keep it all for yourself of did you give some to your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no, we gave some to mother at home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You didn't have a holiday because it was seasonal work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, it was seasonal work. Seasonal work, and you were paid good wages for the time you were doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you have a uniform or did you supply your own clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, our own clothes. Always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You stopped off at a whole lot of different places did you, all along the line, you had different sort of lodgings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. But we - we always were awful lucky with lodgings. I mean the old landlady at Lowestoft crying every day when we left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 She got so fond of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Yes, she says, oh I'll never see you again, and she used to cry and she - she was awful nice. So we - we got an awful lot - we knew an awful lot of folk down there tool Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How may years did you carry on with that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 I think I was thirteen years down in - in Yarmouth and Lowestoft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 After that what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh I - I was home then and I took up knitting and machine knitting and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 All the year round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Then I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you go out to work again after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Women didn't here abouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Not very often, they do more now you see but - at the same time they're all knitting in their houses so 
it's working, you see. They're - they're working at home with their machine, they earn as much money. Quite a good living in the machine knitting you know just now, yes, been for years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Have you done that through your life, machine knitting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes. I've been machine knitting for years and years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you send it to a shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, to L.J. Smith, he's a big - exporter all over the world, yes. Oh yes, it's a very big firm now and limited company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you were doing the fishing did you ever wish you had another kind of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
No, no. I enjoyed it, I was free because once you were off with the fishing in the year your time was your own and you'd nobody to say, well you do this, you see, you were just with the girls and you would go 
to the theatre, you would go to the dances or anywhere, there were - it wasn't like service or anywhere where you were under a master all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You were very free then for a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Very free you know. We had a very free life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did any of your sisters do that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 There were two of them. That did that, and one stayed at home with father and looked after - and never went away. And one in service.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 One went to service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 One went to - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And one stayed at home and two went with the fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 In those days did you belong to a trade union or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was there one, were you ever asked to join a union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. Never.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you ever think about, as people do now, the employers on one side and the workers on another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No, we were always - our employers was very nice to us. Very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You didn't think of them as a different power group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. Because - they were - they would go south you know before us and they would find our
 lodgings and they took the trouble to go round nice landladies and get comfortable lodgings and the employer and his wife always came and visited us, see if we were quite comfortable. And they would do the same on a Sunday now and again. But they weren't
 - they were no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 distinction}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  then what's now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 They really took an interest in seeing you were comfortable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
They really did. And if you were ill or anything you know they would - they would see to you right away. They were very good. I must say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How many girls were on one group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
You were all in three. If possible, that was the easiest way to work you see, and - for - if another one was left out or a neighbours was ill you would take them in to work with you and that come to four of y
ou but more difficult but it'd been all right. But there were always six that stayed together, the two crews you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 There were six with a crew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes. Six girls together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you went to work do you think it changed your way of looking at life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, I don't think - no, I don't think it changed that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Would you say that your life when your were at home, was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 leisure}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  time different from how it had been when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. We just had the same fun. Went to dances, yes, the same friends and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you ever have a cinema show or a magic lantern?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh there were magic lantern, quite a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But not a cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When did you first see a cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well - I'll tell you - I can't - the first one I saw in Shetland was Al }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100796\charrsid13915736 
Jolson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 , Sonny Boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 That must have been around about 1945?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, no, it was long before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 1930 sometime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, it was before the war. It was the first singing picture, the first - 
sound picture was it. But it was Al Jolson. It was up in Lerwick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 What about plays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh they always had that - every village would have its own concert party of plays you know and they would put in, then you would go to some of the halls, I don't think there's a hall in Shetland that's I've not been on a platform. Plays and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did they act plays with learning the parts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes. Yes, we had - plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 You continued going to Sunday school for how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh I think I was fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 About the time you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Then we went to a Bible class after that, the teenagers. That was after the evening service. We'd an hour then Bible study.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Your parents were interested in politics, did you get interested too when you were a teenager?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
No, no. Not as a teenager. I couldn't care less. It's just in recent years that I was interested in - well I can't say that I'm extremist anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But you take an interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, I take an interest and I vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When
 you left home and went on the fishing did it change your way of being when you were at home, did you feel differently about your home in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No, just the same, I - I was glad when - I was glad to go to the fishing but I was just as glad again to be home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And you were the same with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 How many rooms were therein the house where you grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Well the first house before we - our house there was three rooms and a small - outer sort of roo
m. And then when our house was built over there in 1910 there were one, two, five rooms. Five rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 That was quite big for that time wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you had the three rooms can you tell me what the different rooms were, how they were used at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 The first rooms? Oh the first house we had - a - a kitchen sitting room you know and then there were two beds there and that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Would that be two in each bed or one in each?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes, two in - like the ti
er beds that they have now. Yes. Bunk beds, yes. The girls slept at that beds you see. Yes. Father and mother had a bed and the boys had a bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 So you had three rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 And the children would split up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 If people came in to sit and talk in the evening did the girls have wait to go to bed until they'd gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
Oh yes. Yes. But that was no - that was no hardship, we were quite happy. See, not working - going out to a job in the morning you didna matter have you - if you overslept a bit, it wasna like having the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When the children were very small did they sleep with the mother and father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh no, we slept in the room, the - the youngest two always slept with the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 With the parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, until they could trot off in their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you have a set time you were supposed to be in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It varied did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 It varied. Even as children it varied. On Friday nights when we didn't have to go to school on Saturday there was no restrictions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Did you sometimes stay up quite late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. I was up quite late many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 About ten o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh sometimes eleven. But then that would be on - at the weekend on that. But when we was going to school and up in the morning and
 - put earlier to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you put to bed by your mother, did she tuck you in and that kind of thing when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Not when we were bigger girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 But when you were five or six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Oh yes, when we were little - or we had our auntie or a grandmother. Someone would always see us in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 When you were children do you ever remember your parents ever having to tell you not to swear, did you pick up swear words?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes. Yes, you picked it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Was it considered bad to swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, they used to say, not to do that and don't say that words and then you would wonder just what you were saying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 The ideas you had about how to live, what was right and wrong, did you get it more from your mother or more from your father or the same?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 
I think the same. They were both instructors. And father would instruct then mother would instruct even the neighbour children. Especially the teenagers. Watch you-self and do nothing that you would - you wouldn't do before your parents. W
ell it give you an idea not to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6513415\charrsid13915736 do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736  things, you know, it was very good counsel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid525380 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Were there a lot of dances then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12518656 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4943760\charrsid13915736 Yes, there were quite a few.
\par }}